SIMPLE: wheeler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheeler
<hw>Wheel"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who wheels, or turns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A maker of wheels; a wheelwright.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A wheel horse. See under <er>Wheel</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A steam vessel propelled by a
paddle wheel or by paddle wheels; -- used chiefly in the terms
<xex>side-wheeler</xex> and <xex>stern-wheeler</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A worker on sewed muslin.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European goatsucker.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheelhouse</ent>⟦br⟧
